<TITLE> KFC Japan says glass found in salad, 2 hurt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 TOKYO, June 1 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Small pieces of glass were found in food sold at two outlets of restaurant chain Kentucky Fried Chicken Japan Ltd., the company said on Friday. The glass came from a broken thermometer in a refrigerator at a vegetable factory and had fallen onto shredded cabbage, it said in a statement. Two customers complained of hurting their teeth on the glass. One man said his tooth chipped when he chewed a glass shard, and another said a filling fell out, a KFC spokesman said. The company suspended sales of dishes containing shredded cabbage at its 228 outlets across Japan
